WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.609 --> 00:00:07.899
THIS WEEK AT INTERIOR…

00:00:07.899 --> 00:00:13.110
IT WAS WORLD WILDLIFE DAY THIS WEEK, A DAY
SET ASIDE TO CELEBRATE THE INCREDIBLE DIVERSITY

00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:17.770
OF WILDLIFE, WHILE RAISING AWARENESS ABOUT
THE THREAT OF POACHING AND WILDLIFE TRAFFICKING…

00:00:17.770 --> 00:00:21.860
SECRETARY JEWELL TWEETED A SPECIAL VIDEO TO
MARK THE OCCASION, AND SPREAD THE HASHTAG

00:00:21.860 --> 00:00:24.239
*SERIOUS ABOUT WILDLIFE CRIME*.

00:00:24.239 --> 00:00:28.250
OVER 100,000 AFRICAN ELEPHANTS ALONE HAVE
BEEN KILLED FOR THEIR IVORY OVER THE LAST

00:00:28.250 --> 00:00:32.880
FEW YEARS, TENS OF THOUSANDS CONTINUE TO BE
KILLED EACH YEAR, ALONG WITH THOUSANDS OF

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:33.880
RHINOS.

00:00:33.880 --> 00:00:38.270
THE FISH AND WILDLIFE SERVICE DEVOTED A SPECIAL
WEBCHAT TO WORLD WILDLIFE DAY BY SHINING A

00:00:38.270 --> 00:00:41.820
SPOTLIGHT ON THE NATIONAL WILDLIFE FORENSICS
LAB IN ASHLAND OREGON…

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:46.900
THAT’S WHERE A TEAM OF WORLD RENOWNED FORENSIC
EXPERTS WORK TO IDENTIFY PERPETRATORS OF WILDLIFE

00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:49.600
CRIME AND HELP BRING THEM TO JUSTICE.

00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:53.610
FISH AND WILDLIFE THIS WEEK ANNOUNCED 45-MILLION
DOLLARS IN GRANTS THAT WILL BE GOING OUT TO

00:00:53.610 --> 00:00:57.489
STATES TO SUPPORT WILDLIFE, HABITATS AND IMPERILED
SPECIES.

00:00:57.489 --> 00:01:02.070
DIRECTOR DAN ASHE SAYS THE PROGRAM FUNDS THE
HIGHEST PRIORITIES IN EACH STATE TO EFFECTIVELY

00:01:02.070 --> 00:01:05.680
CONSERVE AND PROTECT SPECIES ON A LARGE LANDSCAPE
SCALE…

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:08.740
YOU CAN FIND THE STATE BY STATE BREAKDOWN
AT FWS.GOV.

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:13.640
DEPUTY INTERIOR SECRETARY MIKE CONNOR IS SET
TO HOLD A LISTENING SESSION MARCH 19TH WITH

00:01:13.640 --> 00:01:17.970
TRIBAL LEADERS AND INDIVIDUAL LANDOWNERS TO
TAKE FEEDBACK ON THE PROGRESS OF THE LAND

00:01:17.970 --> 00:01:19.280
BUYBACK PROGRAM…

00:01:19.280 --> 00:01:23.430
THE PROGRAM THAT PURCHASES TRIBAL LAND WITH
MULTIPLE OWNERS, THEN HOLD THE PROCEEDS IN

00:01:23.430 --> 00:01:26.200
TRUST FOR THE ECONOMIC BENEFIT OF THE TRIBE.

00:01:26.200 --> 00:01:30.020
ASSISTANT SECRETARY FOR INDIAN AFFAIRS KEVIN
WASHBURN WILL ALSO TAKE PART.

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:36.400
SO FAR THE LAND BUYBACK PROGRAM HAS PAID NEARLY
340-MILLION DOLLARS AND RESTORED MORE THAN

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:38.560
540-THOUSAND ACRES OF TRIBAL LAND.

00:01:38.560 --> 00:01:42.659
THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE THIS WEEK MADE ITS
OFFICIAL PREDICTION OF DATES FOR WHEN WASHINGTON

00:01:42.659 --> 00:01:45.740
DC’S SIGNATURE CHERRY BLOSSOMS WILL REACH
THEIR PEAK BLOOM…

00:01:45.740 --> 00:01:50.780
APRIL 11TH TO APRIL 14TH, ABOUT A WEEK LATER
THAN AVERAGE, THANKS TO A LONG COLD WINTER.

00:01:50.780 --> 00:01:54.520
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF TOURISTS TURN OUT
EVERY YEAR TO MARVEL AT THE BLOSSOMING TREES,

00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:57.799
A GIFT TO THE U-S FROM JAPAN BACK IN 1912.

00:01:57.799 --> 00:02:01.869
THIS YEAR’S CHERRY BLOSSOM FESTIVAL IN THE
NATION’S CAPITAL RUNS FROM MARCH 20TH THROUGH

00:02:01.869 --> 00:02:03.530
APRIL 12TH.

00:02:03.530 --> 00:02:06.340
AND THIS WEEK IS CROWDED WITH BIRTHDAYS AND
ANNIVERSARIES…

00:02:06.340 --> 00:02:10.060
SATURDAY MARCH 7TH MARKS THE 50TH ANNIVERSARY
OF BLOODY SUNDAY…

00:02:10.060 --> 00:02:15.090
THAT FATEFUL DAY IN 1965 WHEN CIVIL RIGHTS
MARCHERS WERE SET UPON BY POLICE AT THE EDMUND

00:02:15.090 --> 00:02:20.290
PETTUS BRIDGE IN SELMA ALABAMA, SPURRING THE
VOTING RIGHTS ACT AND THE CIVIL RIGHTS MOVEMENT…

00:02:20.290 --> 00:02:23.870
THE USGS TURNED 136 YEARS OLD THIS WEEK…

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:27.870
WHILE YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK MARKED ITS
143RD BIRTHDAY.

00:02:27.870 --> 00:02:34.170
ON MARCH 4TH 1865 - 150 YEARS AGO - PRESIDENT
LINCOLN MADE HIS SECOND INAUGURAL ADDRESS,

00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:36.790
WITH MALICE TOWARD NONE, AND CHARITY FOR ALL.

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.980
SECRETARY JEWELL WILL BE AMONG THE SPEAKERS
AT A SPECIAL CEREMONY COMMEMORATING THAT EVENT

00:02:40.980 --> 00:02:43.170
AT THE LINCOLN MEMORIAL ON SATURDAY…

00:02:43.170 --> 00:02:48.620
AND YOUR DEPARTMENT OF THE INTERIOR CELEBRATED
ITS 166TH BIRTHDAY ON MARCH 3RD, MARKING THE

00:02:48.620 --> 00:02:51.310
DAY THE DEPARTMENT WAS FOUNDED IN 1849.

00:02:51.310 --> 00:02:53.530
THAT’S THIS WEEK AT INTERIOR.

